-- Hungary court rules against Erste Bank in loan refunds case
-- By Marton Dunai
-- Wed Sep 10, 2014 08:51AM EDT
-- None



BUDAPEST, Sept 10 (Reuters) - A Hungarian court rejected on Wednesday a lawsuit brought by the local unit of Austrian Erste Bank <ERST.VI> to challenge a new law mandating refunds to clients on loans, Judge Csaba Balsai said.

The first-degree ruling is open to appeal.